value.0: She lives in the slums with an ailing brother, surviving off the charity of those about her in a small commune.

Many of the refugees that have fled for Veles quickly find themselves homeless, with Czerka largely being callous and apathetic about their plight. A few manage to find opportunities to better their lives, but most languish in shelters and tents, while many join the many predatorial gangs that now prowl the streets of the slums and industrial districts.

This one has gathered to her a growing and loyal band of those who chaff under Czerka's oppression, who seek to carve out a better life, not merely for themselves, but for as many of the refugees as they can. They battle other gangs for control of the slums even as they seek to shield any whom they could find from Czerka, and they are largely based out of an old, abandoned cantina in the slums.
He seems to be terminally ill...

Once in a while, those who are banished to the slums would seek to rebel against what they deem to be Czerkan tyranny and oppression. These tend to be sporadic, unorganized, and often do Czerka catch wind of these movements before they even had the chance to grow. It is not uncommon for gangs of Czerka Rangers to raid the slums, and nip these seeds of resentment before they can even sprout...
Few things last in the slums, the sandcastles of hopes and ambitions oft torn down as swiftly as they are built up...
